name: Koodous
description: This app integrates with Koodous to analyze APK files

actions.description: Validate the asset configuration for connectivity using supplied configuration
Run the file in the sandbox and retrieve the analysis results
actions.verbose: File detonation may take a while. If the polling in this action doesn't succeed in getting the file analysis (which will be indicated through the analysis_complete key in the summary), then you should continue polling with the get report action. If the analysis_type is 'yara' and force_yara_analysis is false, then the 'yara' analysis will only be performed if it has not been performed before. To perform yara analysis repeatedly, keep force_yara_analysis as true.

vault_id.description: Vault ID of file to detonate

attempts.description: Number of attempts to make while polling

actions.description: Query for results of an already completed detonation
actions.verbose: Either the sha256 or vault_id should be specified. If both are specified, the vault_id parameter will be used. You do not need to be the one who detonated a file to retrieve a report. As long as you know the sha256 (or, have the file in the vault) of the APK you want to analyze, you could run this action. The attempts parameter is how many times this action will poll for analysis results. By default, this number is only 1. If you are polling after detonate file timed out, then you will want to increase this to a higher number. There will be a 30 second interval between each polling attempt.

sha256.description: SHA256 hash of file to get analysis of

vault_id.description: Vault ID, will check if there is an existing report for this file

attempts.description: Number of attempts to make while polling
